Broken pen with me :( TFTC

2010-06-04T19:00:00Z : Found it by poohbear50
After a lovely dinnner in a Seafood Restaurant we went for a stroll before returning to our hotel and surprise, surprise WR discovered that we were very close to a cache! He felt that it would be unthinkable not to 'go for it' We were at the cache in a blink of an eye and under the watchful eye of the Harbour Police I signed the log and replaced it safely to its bed. TFTC

2010-06-04T19:00:00Z : Found it by Wild Rover
Post dinner meander around the area had a look at the marina - casually had a sneak look at the GPS and the rest is history. TFTC

2010-06-04T19:00:00Z : Found it by never-there
Nice place, I really like harbors.
TFTC.

2010-05-26T19:00:00Z : Found it by tmob
#2437
We looked for this cache during our holidays in Ireland. Six fantastic days, 1800kms driven, and a bunch of caches found. Definitely a great way to get to know this beautiful island!
After a nice dinner, we went to visit the harbour. The sun was almost down, so the place was pretty clear of people.
Thanks for this one... Greetings from Portugal

2007-08-23T07:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
A nice easy one. After finding CMB50 and I sat and watched a local resident splashing about in the water.
